					<head>Midrash</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>Two fragments of Midrash ha-gadol on Exodus.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="247v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Midrash ha-gadol</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מדרש הגדול</title>
							<note>
								<p>Numeorus marginal notes.</p>
								<p>Ends with parashah Peḳude.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19572491">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19572491" xml:lang="en">Adani, David ben Amram, active 13th century-14th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19572491" xml:lang="he">העדני, דוד בן עמרם</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; two Yemenite semi-cursive script of late 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>247 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>262</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>247 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Signed with Hebrew letters on the last and the first page of a quire.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Numerous folios missing after folio 27, 28, 35, 44. </p>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="27">
									<p>First part of the manuscript (folios 1-27) is undivided, the latter part (folios 28-247) has 2 columns to a page.</p>
									<p>Has marginal notes of chiefly lexical character (inner and outer margins).</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Ruling with a mastara visible.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Two Yemenite semi-cursive script of late 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="27v"/>and <locus from="28r" to="247v"/>- executed by two different but contemporary hands.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
